28:19.890 --> 28:21.027
IP address?
Yes.

28:21.060 --> 28:22.152
Oh, yeah.

28:22.200 --> 28:24.122
It's our little brush with fame.

28:24.170 --> 28:25.228
But you didn't see
Stephanie there

28:25.270 --> 28:26.862
at Copycrater on
the actual day?

28:26.900 --> 28:28.731
The day the e-mail was sent?
No.

28:28.770 --> 28:30.965
All I can tell you
is that she's a customer.

28:31.010 --> 28:33.001
That's all.
RODRIGUEZ: The carpet fibers

28:33.040 --> 28:34.177
found at the crime scene--

28:34.210 --> 28:36.132
they are from a Socala
Tweed Stitch carpet.

28:36.180 --> 28:37.772
And the defendant
owns this carpet?

28:37.810 --> 28:38.947
Yes.

28:38.980 --> 28:41.778
And yet I'm still baffled
why you're here, Detective,

28:41.820 --> 28:43.515
and not at some murder trial.

28:43.550 --> 28:45.211
Can you answer that?
I can't.

28:45.250 --> 28:48.287
All I can say is that
the plaintiff subpoenaed me.

28:52.160 --> 28:53.252
We need another suspect.

28:53.290 --> 28:55.053
See what you can do.
Even the whiff

28:55.100 --> 28:56.249
of another suspect
will help.
Got it.

28:57.300 --> 28:58.995
God, this pisses me off.

28:59.030 --> 29:00.190
Do you think she did it?

29:00.230 --> 29:01.492
Stephanie?
I don't know.

29:01.540 --> 29:03.235
Doesn't matter
if she did.

29:03.270 --> 29:05.033
This lawsuit's
still bogus.

29:25.090 --> 29:28.218
KALINDA: A photo I took earlier
in front of the courthouse.

29:28.260 --> 29:30.455
A gray metallic Audi.

29:30.500 --> 29:33.367
Now here's Stephanie's car,
the photo used in court.

29:33.400 --> 29:35.231
It's what the
valet testified

29:35.270 --> 29:37.135
looked like the car
he saw racing off

29:37.170 --> 29:38.364
on the night
of the murder.

29:38.410 --> 29:40.833
Now, they don't look
much the same, do they?

29:40.880 --> 29:43.303
Until you put
it at the scene

29:43.340 --> 29:47.299
and put it under the same
fluorescent lighting.

29:48.520 --> 29:50.579
Who's this car
belong to?

29:50.620 --> 29:52.144
The widow.

29:53.250 --> 29:54.581
Dana Briglio.

29:54.620 --> 29:57.350
You can point to
her as the killer.

29:57.390 --> 29:59.984
You can't be leaving me,
Kalinda.

30:00.030 --> 30:01.452
You're too good at this.

30:01.500 --> 30:03.422
It's time to move on.

30:03.460 --> 30:05.166
What are you, a Dylan song?

30:05.200 --> 30:07.930
(chuckles)
You said you had my back.

30:13.410 --> 30:16.129
What do you want
from life, Will?

30:17.640 --> 30:19.949
What do I want?

30:19.980 --> 30:21.572
I don't know.

30:21.620 --> 30:23.349
Suddenly, this is about me?
(chuckles)

30:23.380 --> 30:25.883
You want the same things
as Alicia?

30:25.920 --> 30:28.514
Alicia? I...

30:35.330 --> 30:36.558
I don't know.

30:36.600 --> 30:38.227
There's a vast difference
between us.

30:38.270 --> 30:39.999
Because she's married?

30:40.030 --> 30:42.237
Yeah, for one.

30:42.270 --> 30:43.362
And she has kids,

30:43.400 --> 30:45.607
and I...

30:47.110 --> 30:49.374
What are we talking about here?

30:50.410 --> 30:52.105
She separated from her husband.

30:53.380 --> 30:55.541
What?

30:55.580 --> 30:58.378
Alicia--

30:58.420 --> 31:01.412
she separated
from Peter.

31:12.600 --> 31:14.158
It's not...

31:18.240 --> 31:20.265
There are too many issues.

31:20.310 --> 31:21.470
(sighs)

31:21.510 --> 31:23.239
I know.
There always are.

31:23.280 --> 31:26.306
Why?

31:26.350 --> 31:27.476
Why'd they separate?

31:29.450 --> 31:31.941
It's not public knowledge,
so don't tell her I told you.

31:31.990 --> 31:34.379
I'm not going to tell her
anything.

31:34.420 --> 31:36.285
You know best.

31:38.290 --> 31:41.225
(door opens and closes)

31:53.310 --> 31:55.301
(elegant music plays,
indistinct chatter)

32:01.750 --> 32:03.718
JACKIE:
Full confession...

32:03.750 --> 32:06.617
At one point early in
the race, I actually
thought Peter might lose.

32:06.650 --> 32:08.151
Excuse me.

32:08.190 --> 32:09.714
Sorry to interrupt.

32:09.760 --> 32:11.523
Alicia, hello.
What a surprise.

32:11.560 --> 32:12.686
Do you have a moment?

32:12.730 --> 32:14.459
I do.

32:14.500 --> 32:17.355
I know you've heard me talk
about her quite a bit,

32:17.400 --> 32:19.994
but allow me to
Introduce...

32:21.740 --> 32:25.460
Alicia, this really
is a surprise.

32:25.510 --> 32:28.229
From now on, Jackie,
when you want

32:28.280 --> 32:30.532
to come to my home,
you will call me.

32:30.580 --> 32:33.447
If you can't get me,
call my assistant.

32:33.480 --> 32:36.472
If you can't get her,
try again.

32:37.450 --> 32:39.486
Why are you so
upset, Alicia?

32:39.520 --> 32:41.385
Jackie, do you hear my voice?

32:41.420 --> 32:42.648
Do I sound upset?

32:42.690 --> 32:46.353
No, but these words
are so hostile.

32:46.390 --> 32:49.450
The next time you try
to turn my children against me,

32:49.500 --> 32:51.491
I will keep them
permanently off-limits to you.

32:51.530 --> 32:53.498
I didn't try anything.

32:53.530 --> 32:55.498
I... H tried to explain,

32:55.540 --> 32:58.031
because no_o_ne else
Is explaInIng.

32:58.070 --> 33:00.630
Jackie, I have come
to understand

33:00.670 --> 33:03.503
that you need
to hear things two times

33:03.540 --> 33:06.043
to absorb them,
so the next time

33:06.080 --> 33:08.378
you try to turn my
children against me...

33:08.420 --> 33:12.345
So disrespectful.
I watched over them.

33:12.390 --> 33:14.210
Yes, and thank you.

33:14.260 --> 33:16.182
That's why I'm not cutting them
off immediately.

33:16.220 --> 33:18.529
They're Peter's children, too.

33:18.560 --> 33:21.051
Yes, but they're not yours.

33:23.100 --> 33:24.567
He'll get custody.

33:24.600 --> 33:27.694
That's unlikely.

33:27.730 --> 33:29.539
He's the State's Attorney.

33:29.570 --> 33:31.629
Who banged a hooker 18 times.

33:31.670 --> 33:33.433
Let's see where that ends up.

33:33.470 --> 33:35.108
Oh, my God, you're awful.

33:35.140 --> 33:37.176
You don't know the half of it.
The next time you want

33:37.210 --> 33:38.746
to see your grandchildren,
you call first.

33:40.480 --> 33:43.472
I know what happened
in your house.

33:45.450 --> 33:48.317
I was your housekeeper,
you know.

33:48.360 --> 33:52.558
I have no idea
what that means, Jackie.

34:00.570 --> 34:03.391
VALET: Yep, like I said, that's
the car I saw skidding off.

34:03.440 --> 34:05.237
WILL: You saw this
at St. Martin?

34:05.270 --> 34:07.500
Yes.

34:07.540 --> 34:09.201
But this is Dana Briglio's car.

34:11.480 --> 34:13.175
NANCY:
Excuse me.

34:13.210 --> 34:14.643
Objection, Your Honor.

34:14.680 --> 34:16.318
Okay. On what grounds?

34:16.350 --> 34:18.545
Relevance.

34:18.590 --> 34:21.081
What are they suggesting,
that Mrs. Briglio

34:21.120 --> 34:23.213
killed her own husband?
Yes, that's exactly

34:23.260 --> 34:25.558
what we're suggesting.
Thank you, Miss Crozier.

34:25.590 --> 34:26.420
That's ridiculous.

34:26.460 --> 34:27.484
No more ridiculous

34:27.530 --> 34:30.249
than suggesting
our client did it.

34:30.300 --> 34:33.189
I think I have to overrule that,
Miss Crozier.

34:33.230 --> 34:35.095
You introduced
the car eVIdence;

34:35.140 --> 34:36.835
they should be allowed the
opportunity to refute it.

34:36.870 --> 34:40.431
Thank you, Your Honor.

34:40.470 --> 34:42.438
But isn't the Socala Tweed
Stitch carpet fiber

34:42.480 --> 34:44.471
one of the most common types in
North America?

34:44.510 --> 34:46.705
That's true.

34:46.750 --> 34:49.378
And have you tested
all of the carpets
belonging to Mrs. Briglio?

34:49.420 --> 34:50.409
All of them? No.

34:50.450 --> 34:51.815
Do you think you should?

34:51.850 --> 34:54.284
Nope, I don't recognize her.
You're sure?

34:54.320 --> 34:55.856
She lives just as close
to your shop

34:55.890 --> 34:58.552
as my client Stephanie Engler.

34:58.590 --> 35:01.559
Well, I don't see everybody
who comes in.

35:06.530 --> 35:08.896
WILL: Good job.
Really good job.

35:08.940 --> 35:10.794
I loved seeing
Nancy Crozier's face.

35:10.840 --> 35:13.559
(chuckles) Yeah.
Thanks.

35:13.610 --> 35:15.578
How are you?

35:15.610 --> 35:17.578
Is everything good?

35:17.610 --> 35:20.443
Everything's good.

35:20.480 --> 35:21.549
You?

35:21.580 --> 35:24.743
Yeah, I guess. You know.

35:27.550 --> 35:29.518
If you ever want to talk...

35:29.560 --> 35:31.482
Sure.

35:31.530 --> 35:33.486
Good.

35:33.530 --> 35:35.691
I'm here.

35:35.730 --> 35:37.493
Oh, Kalinda, good.

35:37.530 --> 35:41.466
I want you to
prep Alicia for
the questioning

35:41.500 --> 35:43.365
of Dana tomorrow. Thanks.

35:45.970 --> 35:50.578
Okay, um, I'm still tracing
down PrettiSpecial9's avatar.

35:50.610 --> 35:54.239
It, it seems to be part
of a bigger picture;

35:54.280 --> 35:57.340
possibly two
overlapping drawings.

35:57.380 --> 36:00.315
Um, still haven't found
a match.

36:00.350 --> 36:03.353
Do you want me to get
somebody else to brief you?

36:03.390 --> 36:05.688
You mean someone
who hasn't slept
with my husband?

36:08.330 --> 36:09.649
Yes, you're in pain, Alicia.

36:09.700 --> 36:11.668
I hurt you.
Now do you want

36:11.700 --> 36:12.894
to know the facts?
Of what?

36:12.930 --> 36:14.397
I slept with him once.

36:14.440 --> 36:15.566
Now, I do that.

36:15.600 --> 36:17.568
It means nothing to me,

36:17.600 --> 36:19.864
but I do that.

36:19.910 --> 36:21.571
Look, Alicia, I didn't know you.

36:21.610 --> 36:23.601
I'd never even
seen a pIcture of you.

36:23.640 --> 36:25.642
To me, you were just
a housewife.

36:25.680 --> 36:27.898
Then I met you,
and I liked you.

36:27.950 --> 36:30.475
I liked working
with you.

36:30.520 --> 36:32.738
I liked talking with you.

36:32.790 --> 36:33.779
I felt bad.

36:33.820 --> 36:35.981
I don't like
feeling bad.

36:36.020 --> 36:39.387
Every step of the way
you just looked at me.

36:39.430 --> 36:40.454
And you knew?

36:40.490 --> 36:42.253
Yes.

36:42.300 --> 36:43.824
And I'm an idiot.
I never once thought

36:43.860 --> 36:45.623
that you were my friend out
of some guilt.

36:45.670 --> 36:48.559
Out of some guilty
welfare for poor little me.

36:48.600 --> 36:49.567
That's not why.

36:49.600 --> 36:52.706
I don't have
friends, Alicia.

36:52.740 --> 36:53.559
You were a friend.

36:53.610 --> 36:55.009
And you lied to me.

36:55.040 --> 36:58.407
You said, "That's not true"
about being with him.

36:58.450 --> 36:59.769
Yes.

37:01.780 --> 37:03.816
I'm sorry.

37:03.850 --> 37:05.909
Oh. Okay. Thanks.

37:05.950 --> 37:07.838
Oh...

37:07.890 --> 37:10.017
Now that we've
cleared that up...
. .I'm not .
explaInIng to justIfy...

37:10.060 --> 37:12.221
How was my husband?
Was he good?

37:19.400 --> 37:22.733
I'm... I found another job,
and I'm leaving next week.

37:22.770 --> 37:24.704
Good.

37:37.580 --> 37:39.719
Get out!

37:41.790 --> 37:43.610
(sighs)

38:03.840 --> 38:05.705
*

38:55.900 --> 38:56.719
What?

38:56.760 --> 38:58.864
Well...

39:00.470 --> 39:03.064
We're still confirming, but...

39:03.100 --> 39:07.935
we think your husband
is PrettiSpecial9.

39:07.970 --> 39:10.473
We think he was the one

39:10.510 --> 39:14.549
who wrote to Sean Briglio, and
arranged that last... date.

39:15.780 --> 39:17.145
And we just think you
should be forewarned.

39:17.180 --> 39:19.785
But I...?

39:19.820 --> 39:20.889
What?

39:20.920 --> 39:22.387
DIANE:
Our investigator thinks

39:22.420 --> 39:23.819
it probably was your car

39:23.860 --> 39:26.624
skidding away
from the St. Martin

39:26.660 --> 39:29.788
on the night of the murder,
but your husband was driving it.

39:29.830 --> 39:31.889
And the carpet fibers,
we think, are yours.

39:31.930 --> 39:34.797
From your house, but your
husband tracked them there.

39:34.840 --> 39:37.695
DIANE: And our investigator
showed your husband's photo

39:37.740 --> 39:39.958
to the Copycrater employee,

39:40.010 --> 39:42.729
and he identified
him as being a customer.

39:42.780 --> 39:45.044
You're our client,
Stephanie. Alec isn't.

39:45.080 --> 39:46.945
And that's, that's why we wanted

39:46.980 --> 39:48.709
to tell you.

39:48.750 --> 39:50.809
But why?

39:50.850 --> 39:51.942
Why did he do it?

39:51.990 --> 39:53.116
Yes.

39:53.150 --> 39:54.811
He was jealous.

39:54.860 --> 39:58.853
DIANE: Yes, the violence
of the crime scene,

39:58.890 --> 40:01.927
the castration, would suggest
some passionate emotion.

40:01.960 --> 40:03.848
He was jealous?
ALICIA:
Yes.

40:03.900 --> 40:07.063
Did you talk to him about
sleeping with the victim?

40:07.100 --> 40:10.092
Yeah, but I...

40:12.510 --> 40:14.034
I didn't think he cared.

40:14.070 --> 40:17.039
DIANE:
So, Mrs. Engler,
as your lavwers,

40:17.080 --> 40:18.843
we would advise you
to create some distance

40:18.880 --> 40:20.905
between yourself
and your husband.

40:20.950 --> 40:22.838
WILL:
It's legally smart,

40:22.880 --> 40:24.848
but also, it
might be safer.

40:24.890 --> 40:28.678
Either way, we're in a sticlq
situation with the lawsuit.

40:28.720 --> 40:31.052
The plaintiff can now more
clearly show culpability.

40:31.090 --> 40:32.921
WILL:
Stephanie?

40:43.940 --> 40:45.908
Okay, that didn't go
the way I thought.

40:45.940 --> 40:47.168
She's in love.

40:47.210 --> 40:48.700
All right, negotiate

40:48.740 --> 40:49.968
with Crozier.

40:50.010 --> 40:51.978
Let's try to keep her
liability to a minimum.

40:52.010 --> 40:55.776
She's gonna need it for a
good defense lawyer.

40:55.820 --> 40:57.242
You clearly got
Will Gardner's attention.

40:57.280 --> 40:59.544
He asked me how much
I offered you.

40:59.590 --> 41:01.751
And I figure this is when you
tell me you're staying put.

41:01.790 --> 41:03.985
That was your
plan, right?

41:04.020 --> 41:05.248
To get his bid up.

41:05.290 --> 41:08.088
You think I've
been using you?

41:08.130 --> 41:10.519
I think it wouldn't
be the first time.

41:10.560 --> 41:12.892
Hey, my case is done.

41:12.930 --> 41:15.990
I can start Monday.

41:16.040 --> 41:16.938
Okay.

41:16.970 --> 41:19.564
You'll have to hit
the ground sprinting.

41:19.610 --> 41:22.499
You're going to be going back to
the State's Attorney's office.

41:22.540 --> 41:25.543
Yeah, we closed a deal to handle
their investigative work.

41:25.580 --> 41:28.174
It's easier on their
budget to contract out.

41:28.210 --> 41:32.089
I want you to be my
top dog over there.

41:32.120 --> 41:34.111
(laughs)

41:34.150 --> 41:35.879
Okay. I guess that's funny.

41:35.920 --> 41:37.581
With Peter Florrick?

41:37.620 --> 41:38.951
Yes, he's the new
State's Attorney.

41:38.990 --> 41:40.127
He's bringing
everyone back.

41:40.160 --> 41:43.152
(laughing)

41:44.930 --> 41:46.192
I'm staying.

41:46.230 --> 41:48.733
Good. I need you
on the judge murder.

41:48.770 --> 41:51.136
So, what was that,

41:51.170 --> 41:53.206
your little
three-day walkabout?

41:53.240 --> 41:55.731
I wanted to leave.
Now I don't.

41:55.780 --> 41:57.077
You want me to stay?

41:57.110 --> 41:59.169
I do.

41:59.210 --> 42:00.871
Okay.

42:00.910 --> 42:02.116
Is this about Alicia?

42:02.150 --> 42:03.117
Is what about Alicia?

42:03.150 --> 42:04.219
You leaving.

42:06.750 --> 42:07.910
I'm not leaving.

42:11.930 --> 42:13.022
At some point,

42:13.060 --> 42:17.690
Kalinda, you're going
to have to confide in someone.

42:17.730 --> 42:20.062
No, I don't.

42:20.100 --> 42:22.694
You know what I discovered?

42:24.000 --> 42:26.833
I never have
to coande In anyone.

42:39.620 --> 42:41.315
DIANE:
The only client
harder to represent

42:41.350 --> 42:44.319
than a cop-killer
is a judge-killer.

42:44.360 --> 42:46.328
And forget
the adjective "alleged."

42:46.360 --> 42:48.999
Everyone thinks
our client did it.

42:49.030 --> 42:51.919
This judge was a beloved figure.

42:51.970 --> 42:54.291
Which means we're the bad guys,
so don't expect

42:54.330 --> 42:57.891
any help from
outside these offices.

42:57.940 --> 43:01.808
This is a high-profile,
heavy-coverage trial,

43:01.840 --> 43:04.172
and Childs is going to want
to make it his swan song.

43:04.210 --> 43:06.974
So I want everyone
to put his or her life

43:07.010 --> 43:08.739
on hold
for the next two weeks.

